rialism, representative democracy and mass media, periods often dealt with separately by historians of masculinities.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aHuman bodyzGreat BritainxHistoryy18th century. 0aHuman bodyzGreat BritainxHistoryy19th century. 0aMasculinityzGreat BritainxHistoryy18th century. 0aMasculinityzGreat BritainxHistoryy19th century. 0aMaterial culturezGreat BritainxHistoryy18th century. 0aMaterial culturezGreat BritainxHistoryy19th century. 7aDESIGN / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aBodies.  aDesire.  aEmotions.  aGender.  aManliness.  aMasculinity.  aMaterial Culture.  aUnmanliness.  aWorking-class men.  along nineteenth century.1 aBegiato, Joanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packagez978311128248040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152612858440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526128584423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526128584/original  a978-3-11-128248-0  Manchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packageb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles